Fifth leg absent, fifth pedigerous somite globose. Succeeding somite (genital somite) short, lateral margins rounded; genital somite with genital complex, represented by ventrally protruding genital apparatus. Apparatus with two divergent lappets arising from middle of somite (
Figure 4D
). In lateral view, shaft curved downwards, distal half of lappets bent posteriorly, reaching proximal margin of anal somite (
Figure 5E
). Base of arms with small rounded processes, one on each branch (arrowed in 
Figure 4D
); most specimens with spermatophores partially ejected, protruding between genital lappets (
Figure 4D
